The paper deals with a problem in computational complexity and algorithm design, specifically in the area of satisfiability and optimization of Boolean formulas. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). However, the focus on MaxSAT and the use of polynomial-time algorithms and kernelization techniques make cs.DS and cs.CC the most likely categories.
